  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Burundi: Supporting the Development of a National Labour Migration Policy and Negotiation of Bilateral Labour Agreements (BLAs)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project facilitates the development of a national labour migration policy in order to have a better understanding of the flows and dynamics of migrant workers. Furthermore, the project is aimed at reinforcing the capacity of the Government of Burundi in its negotiations for bilateral agreements for migrant workers with selected Gulf States. IOM works closely with key stakeholders including migrant workers&#x2019; associations, trade unions, employers&#x2019; associations as well as steering committees from different government Ministries. Labour migration data and relevant information has been collected in eight provinces of Burundi which contributed to a situational analysis that will serve as a guideline document in the elaboration of the Burundi National Labour Migration Policy. In addition, IOM completed a 2 days training workshop on Negotiations Techniques for Bilateral Labour Agreements (BLA) in November 2019, with the participation of 30 officials from government Ministries, trade unions, recruitment agencies, as well the civil society organizations. The training has greatly contributed to reinforce the capacity of the national institutions on Labour Migration Policy and BLA&#x2019;s by equipping the steering committee members with skills they will need when negotiating bilateral agreements with governments of the Gulf countries.</narrative>
  </description>
